CONFIRMED genuine skip (#3) — needs the removed Python `gcode`/interpreter binding.

test.sh runs `python3 -mcanon error.ngc`, and canon.py does `import gcode` and
drives the interpreter through the Python `gcode` C-extension (gcodemodule.cc),
checking that an interpreter error (error.ngc: `G2 X1 Y1 I.25 F1`, an arc whose
radius does not close) is raised out to Python. gomc removed the embedded Python
interpreter and its `gcode`/`emc` bindings (g-code preview is now the Go ngcpreview
module over REST), so `import gcode` is unavailable — there is no Python surface to
raise the error to.

Note: the arc-radius-mismatch detection itself is interpreter behaviour and is
still exercised by the standalone-interp arc tests; only the Python-binding error
path is removed.
